dialogue: I'm up? What is "up"?
Congrats, Gary, you just got promoted to contract killer.
We reschedule - he's not even here yet.
Hitmen don't cancel the first meeting.
Hitmen don't exist. What, are we following made-up rules now?
What?
Your alias: "Billy." Let's go.
Oh my God, I'm gonna die.
Oh boy... going off the rails here. C'mon... let's get back on track, Gary.
The reason I'm asking, is because it sounds like to me you're talking about the disposal of a body, which is more risky for me.
So, that was good?
Yeah!
Open and fuckin' shut. You might have just saved a life. How's that feel?
Feels good. Feels really good.
You don't say?
You know, I once saw three pilleated woodpeckers at the same time.
Alright, bye.
Oh, Jesus. Bye!
What?
What? Never mind the sting operation...
Bye, Gary.
Bye.
Geez Louise, he's sweatin' Gary hard.
Do we even know what this guy looks like?
No, but he said he'd be the guy sitting alone reading "Catcher in the Rye."
The hell was that about?
I don't know. He just freaked out. Happens...
Does it?
Madison, if you get this, stay out of the house. I'm hearing some stuff about Ray. Call me...
Are you cool with it, Gary?
Yeah.
What are you doing?
Gary, where are you?! We need you back at the station now.
Yes, now. We got a new development on this Madison Masters.
I'm sorry, I'm gonna, I gotta handle something really quickly and then I'm gonna be right back...
Huh. So, do you think she could be involved in his murder?
There's always a chance, but I would be very surprised. She just seemed so happy. She left her husband, got her own place, just seemed like she was doing really well.
You good with that, Gary?
I think it's a good plan. Very good. So, you send me the address, I'll meet you over there. Let's nail her.
You guys there?
Can you guys hear me?
Loud and clear.
What'd you think?
What did YOU think?
You gave her plenty of rope to hang herself.
Yeah, she seemed pretty honest in there.
What about you, Jasper?
